author: @TheXeriatos
text: from discord.ext import commands client = commands.Bot(command_prefix='!')   # Great when listening for commands # You can still listen for any message by   @client.event async def on_message(message):     # Process message     print(message)     # Process it through Bot     await client.process_commands(message)   @client.command() async def ping():     await client.say('pong')   @client.command() async def repeat(*args):     output = ''     if len(args) > 0:         for item in args:         output += word         output += ' '     else:         output = '!repeat arg1 arg2 arg3...'     await client.say(output)   # Pass context @client.command(pass_context=True) async def which_channel(ctx):     await client.say(ctx.message.channel)   client.run(token)
